\section{Implementation}
\label{sec:implementation}

\subsection{Technology Stack}

Al-Marjaa is implemented using:

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Core Language:} Rust (for performance, safety, and concurrency)
    \item \textbf{NLP Integration:} llama.cpp for local inference
    \item \textbf{ML Runtime:} ONNX Runtime for model execution
    \item \textbf{Build System:} Cargo with feature flags for language selection
    \item \textbf{UI Framework:} Native Rust GUI with RTL support
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Project Structure}

\begin{lstlisting}[caption={Project Structure}]
Al-Marjaa-Language/
+-- src/
|   +-- core/              # Language-independent core
|   |   +-- lexer/         # Unicode-aware lexer
|   |   +-- parser/        # Grammar-agnostic parser
|   |   +-- optimizer/     # Optimization passes
|   |   +-- bytecode/      # Bytecode compiler
|   |   +-- jit/           # 5-tier JIT compiler
|   |   +-- vm/            # Virtual machine
|   |   +-- gc/            # Garbage collector
|   |
|   +-- languages/         # Language-specific configs
|   |   +-- arabic/
|   |   |   +-- keywords.yaml
|   |   |   +-- grammar.yaml
|   |   |   +-- errors.yaml
|   |   |   +-- nlp_model/
|   |   |
|   |   +-- chinese/
|   |   +-- spanish/
|   |   +-- russian/
|   |   +-- hindi/
|   |
|   +-- runtime/           # Standard library
|   +-- onnx/             # ONNX integration
|   +-- ui/               # UI framework
|   +-- cli/              # Command-line interface
|
+-- tools/
|   +-- language-generator/  # Create new language configs
|   +-- model-trainer/       # Train Vibe Coding models
|
+-- examples/
    +-- arabic/
    +-- chinese/
    +-- spanish/
\end{lstlisting}

\subsection{Compilation Pipeline}

The compilation pipeline processes code through multiple stages:

\begin{enumerate}
    \item \textbf{Input Processing:}
    \begin{itemize}
        \item Detect text encoding (UTF-8)
        \item Identify language from configuration or auto-detection
        \item Load language-specific keyword mappings
    \end{itemize}
    
    \item \textbf{Lexical Analysis:}
    \begin{itemize}
        \item Tokenize using language-specific keywords
        \item Handle RTL/LTR text direction
        \item Recognize numeral variants
        \item Produce normalized token stream
    \end{itemize}
    
    \item \textbf{Parsing:}
    \begin{itemize}
        \item Apply grammar rules from configuration
        \item Build Abstract Syntax Tree (AST)
        \item Perform syntax validation
        \item Generate localized error messages if needed
    \end{itemize}
    
    \item \textbf{Semantic Analysis:}
    \begin{itemize}
        \item Type checking and inference
        \item Scope resolution
        \item Symbol table construction
    \end{itemize}
    
    \item \textbf{Optimization:}
    \begin{itemize}
        \item Apply optimization passes
        \item Generate optimized AST
    \end{itemize}
    
    \item \textbf{Bytecode Generation:}
    \begin{itemize}
        \item Compile AST to bytecode
        \item Generate debug information
    \end{itemize}
    
    \item \textbf{Execution:}
    \begin{itemize}
        \item Interpret bytecode (Tier 0)
        \item JIT compile hot paths (Tiers 1-4)
        \item Execute native code
    \end{itemize}
\end{enumerate}

\subsection{Performance Optimizations}

\subsubsection{Text Processing Optimization}

Multilingual text processing is optimized through:

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Cached Normalization:} Normalize Unicode once, cache results
    \item \textbf{Parallel Tokenization:} Tokenize multiple files concurrently
    \item \textbf{SIMD String Operations:} Use vectorized instructions for text processing
\end{itemize}

\subsubsection{JIT Optimizations}

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Type Specialization:} Generate specialized code for observed types
    \item \textbf{Inline Caching:} Cache method lookups
    \item \textbf{Escape Analysis:} Allocate objects on stack when possible
    \item \textbf{Loop Unrolling:} Unroll tight loops for better instruction cache usage
\end{itemize}

\subsection{ONNX Integration}

Machine learning models are loaded and executed directly:

\begin{lstlisting}[caption={ONNX Integration Example}]
// Arabic syntax
نموذج = أونكس.حمّل("resnet50.onnx")؛
نتيجة = نموذج.استدل({"مدخل": صورة})؛

// Chinese syntax
模型 = ONNX.加载("resnet50.onnx")；
结果 = 模型.推理({"输入": 图像})；

// Spanish syntax
modelo = onnx.cargar("resnet50.onnx");
resultado = modelo.inferir({"entrada": imagen});
\end{lstlisting}

