\section{Limitations}
\label{sec:limitations}

This work has several limitations that should be acknowledged:

\subsection{Technical Limitations}

\begin{enumerate}
    \item \textbf{NLP Model Availability:} High-quality NLP models are not available for all languages, particularly low-resource languages. This affects Vibe Coding quality.
    
    \item \textbf{Package Ecosystem:} The package ecosystem is nascent compared to established languages. Building comprehensive libraries takes time and community effort.
    
    \item \textbf{Platform Support:} Mobile SDK is planned but not yet available. Current implementation focuses on desktop platforms.
    
    \item \textbf{IDE Support:} While VS Code extension exists, support for other IDEs is limited.
\end{enumerate}

\subsection{Research Limitations}

\begin{enumerate}
    \item \textbf{Usability Studies:} Formal controlled studies with statistical analysis are needed to quantify the benefits of native-language programming.
    
    \item \textbf{Educational Outcomes:} Longitudinal studies in educational settings are needed to measure learning effectiveness.
    
    \item \textbf{Adoption Metrics:} As an open-source project, real-world adoption metrics are still being collected.
\end{enumerate}

\subsection{Vibe Coding Limitations}

\begin{enumerate}
    \item \textbf{Accuracy Variance:} Vibe Coding achieves 94\% accuracy for simple tasks but only 67\% for complex ones.
    
    \item \textbf{Ambiguity Handling:} Natural language is inherently ambiguous; some descriptions may generate incorrect code.
    
    \item \textbf{Model Dependencies:} Requires substantial computational resources for local NLP models.
\end{enumerate}

